# Git and commits

## Format

Use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):

- `feat:` new behavior
- `fix:` bug fix
- `chore:` tooling, deps, housekeeping
- `docs:` documentation only
- `test:` tests only
- `refactor:` behavior-preserving restructure

Optional scope: `feat(api): add pagination`.

## Agent behavior

- After completing a **functional task** (feature, fix, or coherent chore batch), **offer one suggested commit command** with message already filled, e.g.  
  `git add path1 path2 && git commit -m "fix(auth): handle expired refresh tokens"`
- Keep commits **atomic**: one intent per commit when practical.

Do not rewrite unrelated history or force-push unless the user explicitly requests it.
